    // Another way to define a member function outside the class
} // No semicolon needed here
```

### Key points:
- A semicolon is required after the closing brace of a class, struct, or union definition.
- Individual function definitions, including constructors, destructors, or other member functions, whether defined inside or outside of the class definition, do not require a semicolon after their closing brace.
